channel.title: Rswiki
channel.description:
So once we get the admin account all straightened out for the wiki, is anyone interested in helping keep it clean from spambots and checking user edits?
I am also seeing if Moparisthebest can either upgrade the software or just reinstall it again to the newest version since it hasn't been updated since our version came out which was back in 2013! So quite a long time. I am going to be looking into extensions and such to make things easier for editing, administrating, etc, etc, etc. So please if you would like to help out just reply to this topic and maybe give any suggestions you have. I know some have said they would like it to be structured differently but never really gave any ideas. So if you have some suggestions on how we present the information than please suggest away!

On Topic, hopefully MITB upgrades soon so this doesn’t keep happening, I do have a question. Seeing as it looks like we’re pushing to revamp the Wiki, will there be information added that isn’t what’s been there forever? Like instead of just the packet documentation, we have more things related to the pages for JAGGRAB and OnDemand,

Providing documentation on topics such as networking/security, maps, even deeper info on cache formatting and what not. Obviously not plain tutorials because that’s not what documentation is directly meant for, but have more of a learning aspect to it.[/quote]We are in the process of migrating the wiki to github’s wiki management system, Gollum. Until then no work will be done unfortunately. The plan is for me to correct/flesh out the 317 packets first since some information is missing and then to make the player updating easier to read. t4 has a lot of 377 documentation available which I need him to fetch for me again since I lost it a long time ago, so that stuff should be up soon too.
